How Our Crating Process Works

Crating success starts with a clear, collaborative approach. Our process includes:

Step 1: Consultation & Project Assessment

We begin by understanding your cargo, shipping plan, handling requirements, and timeline.

Step 2: Onsite or In‑House Evaluation

We measure and assess the item on‑site or in our facility to capture exact dimensions and handling needs.

Step 3: Design & Engineering

Custom design plans are created based on cargo specs, handling conditions, and transportation environments.

Step 4: Construction & Quality Assurance

Professional craftsmen build your crate using premium materials and structural supports. Each crate undergoes inspection before delivery.

Step 5: Delivery & Logistics Support

We deliver and prepare your custom crate for transit, storage, or pickup—coordinating with carriers as needed.

